<br>
There actually is a great deal of interest in role-play on this server, it's just that for a lot of people the opportunities do not seem to be there.  I was rather pleased by some of the inquiries I received from fellow players about the event after it had happened, showing interest in perhaps participating in future events.  <br>
<br>
The sad thing is that so many people do not bother to read the FV board here, and in so not doing, missed an event they might have joined.  Perhaps with a really big event, we could have a GM give a server-wide anouncement something to the effect of &quot;To those interested, a ROLE-PLAYING event....etc...<br>
<br>
The Necropolis and The Fellowship are definately the present keys to organizing events right now.  My own interest in this server was at a low until I happened to drop into the Necropolis, the channel and board info given to me by one of the dark as I was inquiring around about possable guilds to join.<br>
------------<br>
<br>
As for the term Drow...I like it still being used, as a slang term for dark elves.  This does not mean of course that if you call yourself a 'Drow' that you have to worship the Spider Queen.  Though it might be noted that there are half spider half dark elven creatures roaming about.  Lore has it that Mayong created these creatures.  One could, I suppose, Consider the 'Teir'Dal a sub race of dark elves, the 'Drow' another sub race of the same.   Like a different house...<br>
---------<br>
<br>
On houses, Well, there is the Ebon Storm, the Twilight Dark, and quite a few others, I would love to see the dark elven guilds get together and perhaps rename themselves and call them 'houses'.  With a communal board for these houses to communicate with each other.  The necropolis could be used temporarily for that, under the open area general posting thread I suppose.  <br>
Will definately watch what you can come up with for the role-playing board too.<br>
--------------<br>
<br>
We are overdue for a war between lights and darks, Neriak and the High and Wood Elves.   <br>
Perhaps the forces of Mistmoore, represented by the Horsemen of Mistmoore?  Could organize an attack on those who threaten their existance with their constant raiding of Mayong's estate?   Of course, the real drawback to attacking in the greater Faydarks is the faction hit you would get there dueling....<br>
Time to complain to the developers about the broken guildwar function again.   <br>
--<br>
<br>
The reason I say this is because I have heard some people, who were newbies at the time, say how cool this war was, inspite of not being able to participate in it.    (This might have been one involving the two leagues, Of Shadow and of Honor), and inspite of the griefers who drew the guards over to the combatants, it seems the majority of low levels at that time actually appriciated the enertainment/change in pace from just going around slaying things to level up.<br>
---<br>
<br>
Anyways, my long-winded two-cent's worth....<br>
Role-play lives! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roninsenshi>RoninSenshi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senshi No Adakia<br>Jihad on that ass!</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/10/03 5:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=337.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Shintou.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some thoughts on RP for FV</span><hr size=1> Their was a RP guild for DEs out somewhere.. ones for EQ ..<br>
