<br>
I as a player am VERY behind playing a race as it should be played, and as GM for some 21 years of table top I love to dig for info on stuff if I'm going to bring a character into a game. I've always felt if you are going to be serious about playing a race you should take the time to read up on them. The info is out there if you know where to look. Also the EQRPG has some useful information on the races and cultures of Norrath. Its definately worth a look. I know for some people RPing on FV is their first time RPing, but if you do look into the race, you find even more to use for your charcter's plot and how they will behave among the other races they encounter.<br>
<br>
Some players worry about predjudice, or seeming like a &quot;Bad Person&quot; for insulting another character or refusing to help them, but if you are going to play a race that has distrust and hatred for other races because of their society, you just aren't playing them to their fullest and showing others why they should hate you. After all, how else can you really have good if their isn't a darkside to compare yourself with? Good is considered good for its tolerance, justice, mercy and compassion. Evil is considered Evil for their predjuce, blind hatred, cruelty, and malice toward anything that doesn't fit into what they believe right. Does that mean that there aren't acceptions? No...of course there are, but those &quot;exceptions&quot; usually have a VERY hard time finding a place to fit in. Look at how hard it was for Drizzt in the Darkelf Trilogy. Even after stomping around the North of Faerun for decades he still has to deal with all the predjudice and hatred that coems along with his heritage. What you are just isn't that easy to shake in other's eyes when you don't act like the rest of your race.<br>
<br>
I do as a player take the time to let other players know OOC that its all IC and I personally have no malice toward them...just playing my character as I feel he should be. I'm not a evil bastard...I just play one on EQ.....for the most part. *smriks* What I've found is great though is when you find a good RPer of the opposite side and can spend a evening taunting and tossing insults in good fun. I had a blast one night with a Halfling Druid and Froglok Pally in LS one night like that. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Does a evil charatcer see himself as &quot;evil&quot;? My Character doesn't. Why? Because to him he is just living his life in a society that encourages those beliefs, and to him they are right and everyone else is wrong...period. To him the &quot;good&quot; races are &quot;evil&quot;. Why? Well, the light races kill our guards, attack our cities, and kill us on site for just existing. To him it is them that are wrong. There is no understanding and tolerance. To a Darkelf, anything not a Darkelf is a tool to be used and manipulated, or a target to be killed. Ogres, Trolls, &amp; Humans or others that follow evil gods are allies only because they serve a common goal and similar mindset. There is no understanding for something &quot;differant&quot;. Does that mean my character wouldn't work with someone who claimed to be evil? No...he probably would. Would he allow them into his House? Doubtful. The sigmata that would come from allowing something into his House that the evil society he came from wouldn't accept would be too great to risk for one individual. Yes, its not fair, its not accepting, and its not nice....thats why they are called Evil. Does that mean he isn't cordial and friendly with other darkelves or even other evil races? Of course he is......everyone needs allies. Does that mean he trusts his allies? No....cause they are Evil. *shrugs* <br>
<br>
I have to say I'm very impressed with the amount of info that is on the FV RP Zone on races. Good work in trying to get as much of it in one place as you can. On <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://users.zoominternet.net/~carpenoctem" target="top">our web site</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> we have a History page where we've placed links on historical events, but its nice to see a group of people working toward the same goal for all players. If there is any info you can use from our site to add to what you have already...please do. <br>
<br>
